This paper discusses natural language processing (NLP) tasks and transfer learning, which are typically associated with the computer science sub-category of "Computation and Language" (cs.CL). The paper specifically focuses on neural language models, which are a type of machine learning model, and investigates the use of pre-trained embeddings to improve their performance. This suggests that the paper may also be relevant to the sub-categories of "Machine Learning" (cs.LG), "Artificial Intelligence" (cs.AI), and "Neural and Evolutionary Computing" (cs.NE). Additionally, the paper mentions the use of embeddings in domain classification, which could potentially relate to the sub-category of "Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition" (cs.CV).
